{\an8}The word for "dirt."

76
00:05:01,834 --> 00:05:02,669
Dirt!

77
00:05:04,270 --> 00:05:05,138
Thank you.

78
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:06,939
Don't do it out of the blue!

79
00:05:07,006 --> 00:05:08,141
Who made you do it?

80
00:05:08,541 --> 00:05:09,475
Who made him do it?

81
00:05:09,542 --> 00:05:12,445
<i>It's an expression
of their love to entertain.</i>

82
00:05:13,246 --> 00:05:15,348
Good morning.

83
00:05:19,052 --> 00:05:22,522
<i>On this day, Naniwa Danshi
and other central members</i>

84
00:05:23,089 --> 00:05:26,092
<i>have come together to talk about
the end-of-year performances.</i>

85
00:05:31,998 --> 00:05:35,735
<i>There is a reason why
the members are nervously waiting.</i>

86
00:05:39,839 --> 00:05:41,107
Good morning.

87
00:05:42,842 --> 00:05:47,280
{\an8}<i>Ohkura from Kanjani∞
is joining in on the meeting too.</i>

88
00:05:47,347 --> 00:05:52,185
{\an8}TADAYOSHI OHKURA

89
00:05:53,019 --> 00:05:55,121
For the Christmas medley,

90
00:05:55,188 --> 00:06:00,326
I was thinking of doing it like a show.

91
00:06:00,626 --> 00:06:01,994
Whatever song you're doing,

92
00:06:02,495 --> 00:06:04,764
I don't know how much
the fans will understand,

93
00:06:04,831 --> 00:06:07,500
but you should start raising your game.

94
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:11,971
<i>That was when the frontman,</i>

95
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:13,606
<i>Daigo Nishihata, spoke up.</i>

96
00:06:13,873 --> 00:06:16,509
I want to give the spotlight
to the little kids.

97
00:06:17,009 --> 00:06:18,144
Rather than me.

98
00:06:19,512 --> 00:06:20,713
Like in ANOTHER?

99
00:06:21,247 --> 00:06:24,217
<i>What members will they choose,
and what songs will they sing?</i>

100
00:06:24,851 --> 00:06:26,352
<i>Amid everyone's ideas,</i>

101
00:06:26,853 --> 00:06:31,090
<i>Nishihata has been put in charge of doing
a collaboration with the children.</i>

102
00:06:32,658 --> 00:06:33,993
{\an8}Interacting with them...

103
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:36,229
{\an8}It's fine if it's part of
the choreography,

104
00:06:36,295 --> 00:06:38,631
{\an8}but going up to them while singing

105
00:06:38,698 --> 00:06:41,534
{\an8}and doing things like this
becomes really tiring.

106
00:06:42,535 --> 00:06:45,271
Just being with the kids is tiring.

107
00:06:45,338 --> 00:06:47,640
Yeah.

108
00:06:47,707 --> 00:06:50,042
You should treat it like it's your solo.

109
00:06:50,109 --> 00:06:51,477
-Oh, really?
-Yeah.

110
00:06:53,012 --> 00:06:56,215
<i>As someone who knows the difficulties,
Ohkura gives him advice,</i>

111
00:06:56,549 --> 00:07:00,386
<i>but Nishihata still wants to
focus on the children.</i>

112
00:07:03,122 --> 00:07:06,459
Rather than a solo, I was thinking about

113
00:07:06,793 --> 00:07:09,529
prioritizing the kids during the song.

114
00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:11,898
More than making it my solo.

115
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:13,633
So Daigo,

116
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:16,169
you want to support the younger kids

117
00:07:16,502 --> 00:07:18,271
who just joined?

118
00:07:18,337 --> 00:07:19,071
Yes.

119
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:22,708
You want to nurture them?

120
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:27,213
<i>Creating a performance
where everyone can shine.</i>

121
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:30,316
<i>That is Nishihata's wish.</i>

122
00:07:33,586 --> 00:07:37,423
<i>Now, let's introduce the remaining members
of Naniwa Danshi.</i>

123
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:44,397
{\an8}<i>The leader, with his countertenor voice,</i>

124
00:07:44,797 --> 00:07:45,865
{\an8}<i>is Kazuya Ohashi.</i>

125
00:07:45,932 --> 00:07:47,500
{\an8}KAZUYA OHASHI (AGE 21)

126
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:55,208
-This.
-Yes, I can.

127
00:07:55,274 --> 00:07:56,542
I can sing that.

128
00:07:58,911 --> 00:08:01,714
{\an8}<i>The oldest member, Joichiro Fujiwara,</i>

129
00:08:02,215 --> 00:08:04,617
{\an8}<i>is the gray eminence of Naniwa Danshi.</i>

130
00:08:04,684 --> 00:08:08,621
{\an8}JOICHIRO FUJIWARA (AGE 23)

131
00:08:08,921 --> 00:08:09,789
{\an8}KYOHEI TAKAHASHI (AGE 18)

132
00:08:09,856 --> 00:08:14,327
{\an8}<i>The tall and handsome Kyohei Takahashi
and Shunsuke Michieda.</i>

133
00:08:14,393 --> 00:08:15,194
{\an8}SHUNSUKE MICHIEDA (AGE 16)

134
00:08:15,261 --> 00:08:18,030
{\an8}<i>These two joined Kansai Johnny's Jr.
four years ago,</i>

135
00:08:18,564 --> 00:08:20,967
{\an8}<i>and were chosen to join Naniwa Danshi.</i>

136
00:08:24,837 --> 00:08:26,672
Is your voice still changing?

137
00:08:27,373 --> 00:08:29,375
I don't know.

138
00:08:29,442 --> 00:08:30,810
Is it done?

139
00:08:30,877 --> 00:08:31,711
Maybe.

140
00:08:34,847 --> 00:08:38,050
{\an8}<i>And the mild-mannered classic idol types,</i>

141
00:08:38,584 --> 00:08:41,587
{\an8}<i>Kento Nagao and Ryusei Onishi.</i>

142
00:08:42,154 --> 00:08:44,056
{\an8}<i>They didn't expect to be chosen.</i>

143
00:08:44,123 --> 00:08:45,491
{\an8}RYUSEI ONISHI (AGE 17)

144
00:08:45,558 --> 00:08:46,492
I got a message

145
00:08:46,559 --> 00:08:48,094
from our manager saying

146
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:51,597
they made Naniwa Danshi, a Kansai unit.

147
00:08:51,664 --> 00:08:55,501
It had all the members written down,
but I thought it was a prank at first.

148
00:08:55,568 --> 00:08:57,503
I asked them what it was about,

149
00:08:57,570 --> 00:09:00,039
and they said, "the message explains it."

150
00:09:00,706 --> 00:09:01,908
It wasn't a prank.

151
00:09:02,141 --> 00:09:03,843
Now that we've become a unit,

152
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:06,913
the seven of us can work hard together,
so it's reassuring.

153
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:09,615
More people will come to know us.

154
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:12,051
It's a huge chance.

155
00:09:13,886 --> 00:09:15,321
<i>For these members,</i>

156
00:09:15,755 --> 00:09:19,191
<i>Ohkura spends all the time he can
giving them advice.</i>

157
00:09:20,293 --> 00:09:21,894
<i>What is on his mind?</i>

158
00:09:22,762 --> 00:09:25,431
During the interlude, for example.

159
00:09:26,098 --> 00:09:31,771
There are so many kids here
with such potential and talent.

160
00:09:32,672 --> 00:09:33,539
But...

161
00:09:34,407 --> 00:09:37,009
I feel like they're being overshadowed.

162
00:09:38,210 --> 00:09:40,379
I'm sure they've felt isolated.

163
00:09:41,213 --> 00:09:43,382
Each of them must have felt anxious

164
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:45,751
and probably still do right now.

165
00:09:46,419 --> 00:09:48,554
But they don't know what to do.

166
00:09:48,955 --> 00:09:50,990
When I was a Johnny's Jr. member,

167
00:09:51,157 --> 00:09:52,625
before I was in Kanjani∞,

168
00:09:52,692 --> 00:09:55,061
I wasn't in any unit.

169
00:09:55,895 --> 00:09:59,966
And I didn't have anyone
I could get advice from.

170
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:03,970
When I think about how they've been
in that situation this whole time,

171
00:10:05,738 --> 00:10:09,141
it makes me want to help them
in any way I can.

172
00:10:11,043 --> 00:10:12,345
Who have I not met?

173
00:10:12,778 --> 00:10:13,980
-Me.
-Me.

174
00:10:14,213 --> 00:10:17,817
<i>Not wanting their fellow teammates
to feel isolated.</i>

175
00:10:18,484 --> 00:10:21,053
<i>Nishihata feels the same way as Ohkura.</i>

176
00:10:23,089 --> 00:10:24,824
-What's your name?
-Ryusei Ida.

177
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:26,158
-Ida?
-Ryusei.

178
00:10:26,225 --> 00:10:27,193
-Ryusei?
-Yes.

179
00:10:27,259 --> 00:10:29,895
Like a dragon?

180
00:10:30,663 --> 00:10:32,798
<i>Holding on to big dreams,</i>

181
00:10:33,032 --> 00:10:34,734
<i>these children gather here.</i>

182
00:10:39,905 --> 00:10:42,208
<i>Many of the idols
who are in the limelight now,</i>

183
00:10:42,642 --> 00:10:45,845
<i>including himself,
have all gone down this road.</i>

184
00:10:49,148 --> 00:10:53,586
<i>If possible, he wants them to feel
like they have a chance.</i>

185
00:10:56,789 --> 00:10:58,991
Work hard on the dance routine.

186
00:11:00,559 --> 00:11:03,829
{\an8}<i>Nishihata joined the agency
when he was 14 years old.</i>

187
00:11:09,468 --> 00:11:14,140
{\an8}<i>He was in a unit with Ren Nagase,
who is currently in King & Prince,</i>

188
00:11:14,507 --> 00:11:15,941
{\an8}<i>and they worked hard together.</i>

189
00:11:16,008 --> 00:11:20,012
{\an8}REN NAGASE

190
00:11:21,047 --> 00:11:22,982
<i>He kept his nose to the grindstone</i>

191
00:11:23,449 --> 00:11:26,986
<i>and seized opportunities,
like appearing in dramas by himself.</i>

192
00:11:31,057 --> 00:11:32,358
Good morning.

193
00:11:33,159 --> 00:11:34,660
<i>To meet for our interview,</i>

194
00:11:35,361 --> 00:11:37,430
<i>Nishihata has come by subway.</i>

195
00:11:37,763 --> 00:11:38,664
Let's go.

196
00:11:41,333 --> 00:11:42,234
Let's go.

197
00:11:42,501 --> 00:11:43,803
How do you usually travel?

198
00:11:44,970 --> 00:11:45,938
I use the train.

199
00:11:46,639 --> 00:11:48,708
Pretty much all Johnny's Jr. members
commute by train.

200
00:11:53,245 --> 00:11:56,315
<i>Nishihata has one wish.</i>

201
00:11:57,016 --> 00:12:00,252
<i>That is for all
the Kansai Johnny's Jr. members</i>

202
00:12:00,319 --> 00:12:02,321
<i>to become famous.</i>

203
00:12:03,222 --> 00:12:07,059
<i>That's what he believes his own role
within Naniwa Danshi to be.</i>

204
00:12:09,762 --> 00:12:11,664
One day, I'd like to be

205
00:12:12,698 --> 00:12:17,570
like ARASHI and Kanjani∞,

206
00:12:17,636 --> 00:12:20,740
where no matter who becomes the frontman,
the group still shines.

207
00:12:20,806 --> 00:12:24,510
That's the kind of group that I want
Naniwa Danshi to become.

208
00:12:25,211 --> 00:12:28,414
I don't mean that I'm not cut out
to be the frontman,

209
00:12:28,647 --> 00:12:32,752
it's just that would make us stronger.

210
00:12:33,285 --> 00:12:34,854
It's not easy to make a group

211
00:12:36,522 --> 00:12:40,893
that can shine
no matter who the frontman is.

212
00:12:41,994 --> 00:12:43,562
All of us need to become famous

213
00:12:45,064 --> 00:12:47,066
and be qualified as frontmen.

214
00:12:49,268 --> 00:12:51,403
Not that I'm famous or anything.

215
00:12:51,470 --> 00:12:52,605
I'm not at all.

216
00:12:56,175 --> 00:12:57,877
<i>Mid-November.</i>

217
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:07,153
<i>As the performance nears,
the rehearsals become more rigorous.</i>

218
00:13:07,553 --> 00:13:10,122
<i>Each member is honing their own skills.</i>

219
00:13:15,461 --> 00:13:17,963
<i>Some of those are unique.</i>

220
00:13:21,634 --> 00:13:24,904
<i>During free time in between rehearsals,
this member is studying.</i>

221
00:13:25,871 --> 00:13:28,874
<i>While studying economics
at a national university,</i>

222
00:13:29,108 --> 00:13:31,210
<i>he's also active as a Johnny's Jr. member.</i>

223
00:13:33,445 --> 00:13:36,048
There are idols who do news shows, right?

224
00:13:36,749 --> 00:13:39,218
I want to focus on that area.

225
00:13:39,952 --> 00:13:42,121
We don't have anyone like that right now.

226
00:13:42,388 --> 00:13:44,790
So I wanted to assume that position.

227
00:13:44,857 --> 00:13:46,458
TAISEI FUKUMOTO

228
00:13:47,459 --> 00:13:50,563
<i>And demonstrating
precise dance moves here</i>

229
00:13:50,629 --> 00:13:55,334
<i>is the group of older members
who are the pillars of Kansai Johnny's Jr.</i>

230
00:13:58,337 --> 00:14:00,172
<i>On top of their own performances,</i>

231
00:14:00,472 --> 00:14:02,374
<i>their job is to rev up the crowd</i>

232
00:14:02,708 --> 00:14:04,910
<i>as backup dancers for the younger ones.</i>

