247
00:14:35,507 --> 00:14:36,842
<i>is part of their tradition.</i>

248
00:14:38,244 --> 00:14:39,712
{\an8}<i>MAIDO! JOHNNY</i> FILMING

249
00:14:39,778 --> 00:14:43,816
{\an8}<i>That was clearly eminent during
this day's TV show filming.</i>

250
00:14:47,119 --> 00:14:50,322
{\an8}<i>The two who support the members
who are less experienced</i>

251
00:14:50,656 --> 00:14:53,459
{\an8}<i>with their excellent conversation skills</i>

252
00:14:53,726 --> 00:14:57,363
{\an8}<i>are Koji Mukai and
the eldest member, Ryuta Muro.</i>

253
00:14:57,429 --> 00:15:00,266
{\an8}RYUTA MURO, KOJI MUKAI

254
00:15:00,532 --> 00:15:03,535
{\an8}If someone tries to do
something funny and fails...

255
00:15:03,602 --> 00:15:05,304
{\an8}RYUTO MURO

256
00:15:05,371 --> 00:15:07,606
{\an8}I want to be able to save the situation.

257
00:15:08,607 --> 00:15:10,476
I want to help everyone, you know?

258
00:15:11,944 --> 00:15:16,015
I want to,
because people did the same for me

259
00:15:16,081 --> 00:15:19,451
when I was small.

260
00:15:19,885 --> 00:15:21,820
You're making fun of me.

261
00:15:21,887 --> 00:15:22,988
I can feel it.

262
00:15:23,289 --> 00:15:24,990
Your monologue almost made me cry.

263
00:15:25,057 --> 00:15:25,858
You liar.

264
00:15:26,625 --> 00:15:27,559
{\an8}Good luck.

265
00:15:27,626 --> 00:15:28,494
{\an8}KOJI MUKAI

266
00:15:28,560 --> 00:15:31,397
{\an8}<i>On the other hand,
Mukai is the caring type.</i>

267
00:15:32,932 --> 00:15:35,367
Kyohei is always
fixing his hair like this.

268
00:15:35,434 --> 00:15:36,302
{\an8}KYOHEI TAKAHASHI (AGE 18)

269
00:15:36,368 --> 00:15:37,403
{\an8}-Right?
-Yes.

270
00:15:37,703 --> 00:15:40,506
{\an8}-You do it the most out of everyone.
-Yeah.

271
00:15:41,073 --> 00:15:42,308
{\an8}Good luck.

272
00:15:43,275 --> 00:15:44,276
When are you going?

273
00:15:46,178 --> 00:15:47,613
When are you going to go?

274
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:50,049
<i>They almost seem like brothers.</i>

275
00:15:51,984 --> 00:15:57,122
Johnny's members get costumes
with their names placed on top, like this.

276
00:15:57,189 --> 00:15:58,757
Right now, it's Mukai's, but...

277
00:15:58,824 --> 00:16:00,125
We've all done this.

278
00:16:01,493 --> 00:16:02,494
Inohara!

279
00:16:04,563 --> 00:16:08,167
Like that, new names are placed on top.

280
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:11,770
So everyone goes,
"Whose costume was it?!"

281
00:16:12,738 --> 00:16:14,039
"It was Yamashita's!"

282
00:16:14,373 --> 00:16:16,275
That happens a lot.

283
00:16:17,209 --> 00:16:18,610
-Big bro!
-You work at a nightclub?

284
00:16:18,677 --> 00:16:19,845
Looks like it, right?

285
00:16:19,912 --> 00:16:21,914
<i>There may be a big age gap,</i>

286
00:16:22,448 --> 00:16:23,849
<i>but they're a team.</i>

287
00:16:24,950 --> 00:16:26,218
Big bro.

288
00:16:26,785 --> 00:16:29,455
-Big bro!
-Big bro! So cute.

289
00:16:30,022 --> 00:16:31,256
You're so cute, Big Bro.

290
00:16:33,726 --> 00:16:36,795
<i>In this tough business
where there's no promise of success,</i>

291
00:16:36,862 --> 00:16:38,897
<i>they support each other.</i>

292
00:16:44,803 --> 00:16:47,306
<i>The feeling that they all share
is expressed</i>

293
00:16:47,673 --> 00:16:49,308
<i>in a song written by their senior.</i>

294
00:19:17,789 --> 00:19:20,092
{\an8}<i>Numazu City, Shizuoka Prefecture.</i>

295
00:19:22,361 --> 00:19:25,597
{\an8}<i>Nishihata is on the film set
for a drama series</i>

296
00:19:25,664 --> 00:19:28,000
{\an8}<i>in which he is appearing on his own.</i>

297
00:19:29,835 --> 00:19:31,703
{\an8}<i>He uses any opportunity he can get</i>

298
00:19:32,104 --> 00:19:36,875
<i>to make Kansai Johnny's Jr. and
Naniwa Danshi nationwide household names.</i>

299
00:19:39,411 --> 00:19:45,017
<i>He is playing the role of a Tokyo student
who studies animal behavior, but...</i>

300
00:19:45,517 --> 00:19:47,219
When did you start liking ants?

301
00:19:49,254 --> 00:19:52,758
Relaying interesting facts
is fun, isn't it?

302
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:55,827
Fix your intonation.

303
00:19:56,328 --> 00:19:58,330
"Relaying interesting facts."

304
00:19:58,397 --> 00:19:59,598
"Interesting facts"...

305
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:02,868
"Relaying interesting facts."

306
00:20:03,368 --> 00:20:04,536
"Interesting facts."

307
00:20:04,803 --> 00:20:06,104
"Interesting facts."

308
00:20:06,171 --> 00:20:10,309
<i>He can't help but say things
with a Kansai intonation.</i>

309
00:20:12,744 --> 00:20:15,714
Another time, when I was in a movie,

310
00:20:15,781 --> 00:20:17,683
I had to say, "culture festival".

311
00:20:18,483 --> 00:20:20,586
My intonation for that was different too.

312
00:20:21,353 --> 00:20:24,690
In standard Japanese,
it goes down after the first syllable,

313
00:20:24,756 --> 00:20:27,826
but in the Kansai dialect, it goes up.

314
00:20:28,460 --> 00:20:29,661
But then...

315
00:20:29,728 --> 00:20:34,333
When I'm on set for a long time,
I get used to standard Japanese.

316
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:38,303
So, when I go back home to Osaka,

317
00:20:38,370 --> 00:20:41,974
standard Japanese comes out sometimes
unintentionally,

318
00:20:42,474 --> 00:20:47,179
and they call me gross
and tainted and whatnot.

319
00:20:47,980 --> 00:20:48,847
It's tough.

320
00:20:50,082 --> 00:20:51,016
So tough.

321
00:20:54,486 --> 00:20:57,656
<i>Even in between scenes,
he practices his dance routine.</i>

322
00:21:04,196 --> 00:21:06,331
If people come to know me,

323
00:21:06,398 --> 00:21:08,600
then Kansai Johnny's Jr.,

324
00:21:09,101 --> 00:21:12,971
and now the unit Naniwa Danshi,
will also become known.

325
00:21:13,438 --> 00:21:18,110
So, I need to be the vanguard
and promote them.

326
00:21:18,343 --> 00:21:21,513
I hope that I can get people
at least a little bit interested

327
00:21:22,080 --> 00:21:25,884
in Kansai Johnny's Jr. and Naniwa Danshi.

328
00:21:29,321 --> 00:21:32,391
<i>With preparations for the end-of-year
